  "text": "We construct the compressed, vertical reduction τ consisting of steps τ 0 , τ 1 , . . . as follows. For i ∈ N we let τ i contract a fairly chosen redex, outermost among the redexes of which a descendant is contracted in γ i , and define γ i+1 = γ i /τ i (that is, the projection of γ i over τ i ). Here, by 'fair' we mean that every redex will be chosen after some finite number of steps. Note that the set of redexes of which a descendant is contracted is never empty unless γ i is empty. It can be shown that the thus constructed reduction τ is strongly converging and has the same limit as γ 0 . (In the case of a divergent sequence γ 0 , τ also is divergent.) For more details, we refer to Ketema [CITATION_1] .",
